INSERT INTO `a_tn2_notice_list` VALUES (3,'notice',-3,1,0,NULL,3,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1584316800,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'What is Coronavirus? How to Protect Yourself? ',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'A special lecture about Coronavirus was given by a faithful Chicago UBF member and an infectious disease specialist at Rush University Hospital, Dr. Sarah W., on Friday, March 6, 2020 at Chicago UBF Monthly United Friday Meeting. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,'notice',-4,1,0,NULL,4,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1584316800,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'(NEW) HQ Guidelines for UBF chapters dealing with the COVID-19 (Video)',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'March 14, 2020\r\n\r\nDear UBF leaders,\r\n\r\n\"Let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, since as members of one body you were called to peace. And be thankful.\" (Col 1:15)\r\n\r\nIn order to respond to the threat of the coronavirus (COVID-19), UBF HQ staff, in consultation with the excellent doctors in our community, have been praying about and discussing how we may best meet this challenge. At the moment, HQ hereby gives guidelines for all UBF chapters in dealing with the COVID-19 as below.\r\n\r\nGuidelines for UBF chapters:\r\n\r\n1. Chapter leaders proactively guide public meetings, including Sunday worship service, with wisdom. \r\n- Pray for the help of the Holy Spirit, for God\'s peace and Jesus\' grace to cover us at this time.\r\n- Pray for the well being of the chapter members spiritually, emotionally and physically.\r\n- If anyone in the chapter tests positive for COVID-19, cancel public meetings immediately and seek professional medical treatment.\r\n- It is permissible to stop gathering for Sunday worship service and instead employ social media in virtual worship.\r\n- Consider the wisdom of \"social distancing\" in relation to seating, congregating, singing and greeting. \r\n- Consider limited contact, refrain from hugging, kissing, handshaking, or congregating.\r\n\r\n2. Discourage having large scale conferences and international travel.\r\n\r\n3. Encourage church members who are at risk not to attend Sunday worship service or other public meetings until the threat diminishes.\r\n- Sick children should stay at home with a parent or babysitter.\r\n- Anyone with cold or flu symptoms--cough, fever, sore throat, runny nose, muscle aches, heavy congestion--should stay at home.\r\n- Elderly members and those or high risk due to diabetes, heart disease, lung disease, cancer should stay at home.\r\n\r\n4. Practice good hygiene.\r\n- Make hand sanitizers available.\r\n- Clean high touch surfaces frequently (doorknobs, faucets, toilet flush handles, sinks, etc.).\r\n- Wash your hands regularly throughout the day and for 20 seconds each time.\r\n- Please cover any sneezes or coughs in your elbow and turn away from those nearby.\r\n\r\nMay the grace and peace be with you.\r\n\r\nIn Christ,\r\n\r\nGeneral Director: Moses Yoon \r\nVice General Director: Ron Ward\r\nInternational Coordinator: Mark Vucekovich',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(5,'notice',-5,1,0,NULL,5,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1584403200,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Announcement for LBCC Campus Group Bible Study',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'Dear LBCC coworkers,\r\n\r\nAs Grace shared LBCC will be closed and it will be hard to have group bible study at LBCC. So we will not have Tuesday and Thursday group bible study for a while until situation gets better. \r\nBut we can help students through personal contact.\r\nIf there is any update it will be notified.\r\nCurrent situation really shows us that God wants us to pray during this period of time so that he may do wonderful work of Holy Spirt after all. \r\nLet\'s pray earnestly for our bible students and LBCC ministry during this time so that we may see great work of God! ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(7,'notice',-6,1,0,NULL,6,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Billy Park',0,NULL,1586044800,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CBF Messages are available on YouTube channel',0,'Billy Park','admin','bcjmepark@gmail.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'Thank God for allowing us to create a Los Angeles CBF YouTube channel - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCUzEkRsggzgscWdp_UGFZ2w\r\nEach week, we\'re running an online worship service, record the worship service, and upload the video to this channel. \r\nIf you have any suggestion or question, please feel free to reach out to me at bcjmepark@gmail.com, thank you, Billy Park',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(8,'notice',-8,1,0,NULL,8,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1588464000,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Announcement (5/3/2020)',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'1. Have faith in God. God wants us not only to take care of us but also pray for the salvation of all nations. That is the purpose of God giving us the mountain moving faith. So let us have faith in God and keep praying for the salvation of all nations. \r\n\r\n2. Seek the will of God more than anything else. Think about “What is God doing?” \r\n\r\n3. “If my people, who are called by my name, will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven, and I will forgive their sin and will heal their land.” (2 Chronicles 7:14)\r\n\r\n4. Protection for medical professionals, health care workers, especially our co-workers who are working in the front line of the virus. \r\n\r\n5. Pray for our co-workers around the world who cannot maintain their basic life. \r\n\r\n6. You can bring your offerings to my office or through online Zelle program.  \r\n\r\n7. Follow all government guidelines including social distance. \r\n\r\n8. Use our time as a good opportunity to have faith in God and pray for all nations, and witness Jesus as the Lord. \r\n\r\n9. John  Kwon for the next week’s message\r\n\r\n10. Please contact me or leaders if you need anything such as food or any other essentials.For ourselves also, we can experience God’s abundance in the scarcity when we remember how Jesus fed 5,000 people out of 5 loaves and 2 fish. By bringing what we have to Jesus, together we can experience God’s abundance.\r\n\r\n11. John Kwon for prayer and the Lord’s wisdom ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(9,'notice',-9,1,0,NULL,9,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1590278400,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Announcement (5/24/2020)',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'Announcement May 24, 2020 \r\n\r\n1. We need to practice justice. Most of all, we need to give back to God what is God’s. We can start by bringing our financial offerings that belongs to God first. Then, we can extend it to other areas of our lives. \r\n\r\n2. Seek the will of God more than anything else. Think about “What is God doing?” \r\n\r\n3. “If my people, who are called by my name, will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven, and I will forgive their sin and will heal their land.” (2 Chronicles 7:14)\r\n\r\n4. Protection for medical professionals, health care workers, especially our co-workers who are working in the front line of the virus. \r\n\r\n5. Pray for our co-workers around the world who cannot maintain their basic life. \r\n\r\n6. You can bring your offerings to my office or through online Zelle program.  \r\n\r\n7. Follow all government guidelines including social distance. \r\n\r\n8. Use our time as a good opportunity to learn Jesus’ authority and obey him, and witness Jesus as the Lord. \r\n\r\n9. David Park for the next week’s message.\r\n\r\n10. John Kwon for prayer and wisdom of God\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(10,'notice',-10,1,0,NULL,10,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1590883200,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Announcement May 31, 2020',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'1. God is the God of the living. There is no death in God. We suffer from many elements of death such as fear, anxiety and sickness. But God is not the God of the dead but of the living. God is God of those who are living through faith in him. So let us keep our faith in him and experience his powerful life through the Holy Spirit who dwell in us.\r\n\r\n2. Seek the will of God more than anything else. Think about “What is God doing?” \r\n\r\n3. “If my people, who are called by my name, will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven, and I will forgive their sin and will heal their land.” (2 Chronicles 7:14)\r\n\r\n4. Protection for medical professionals, health care workers, especially our co-workers who are working in the front line of the virus. \r\n\r\n5. Pray for our co-workers around the world who cannot maintain their basic life. \r\n\r\n6. You can bring your offerings to my office or through online Zelle program.  \r\n\r\n7. Overseers have been praying and discussing about how to reopen our church. Thank God we can now reopen our church, using 25% of normal capacity. We sent out the survey about reopening of our church through our emails. Please respond by 6pm Tuesday night. Overseers will meet at 8pm to find the best way to reopen our church based on the information . \r\n\r\n8. Use our time as a good opportunity to learn Jesus’ authority and obey him, and witness Jesus as the Lord. \r\n\r\n9. John Kwon for the next week’s message.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(11,'notice',-11,1,0,NULL,11,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1593907200,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Announcement July 5, 2020',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'1. God blesses us to live by faith in Jesus’ coming. People in Old Testament lived by faith in Jesus’ coming. Now we who live in New Testament period also live by faith in Jesus’ coming. When we live by faith in Jesus’ coming God blesses us with his power and glory. Life of faith can be a Fantastic Adventure In Trusting Him.\r\n\r\n2. Seek the will of God more than anything else. Think about “What is God doing?” \r\n\r\n3. “If my people, who are called by my name, will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven, and I will forgive their sin and will heal their land.” (2 Chronicles 7:14)\r\n\r\n4. Protection for medical professionals, health care workers, especially our co-workers who are working in the front line of the virus. \r\n\r\n5. Pray for our co-workers around the world who cannot maintain their basic life.   \r\n\r\n6. Offering either by Zelle or envelope. It is to share God’s blessings with others. It is to store our treasures in heaven. \r\n\r\n7. Use our time as a good opportunity to preach the gospel as the preparation for Jesus’ second coming.\r\n\r\n8. Follow government guidelines including wearing mask and social distancing. It is a practice of loving our neighbors because we can be carriers of the virus without symptoms.\r\n\r\n9. Please respond to the survey for UBF Summer Bible Conference. We sent it out again with another option of ‘either way is okay’. Please respond by 6pm on the coming Tuesday\r\n\r\n10. William is the next week’s messenger. Please pray for him.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(12,'notice',-12,1,0,NULL,12,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1594512000,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Virtual Vision camp 2020 - Registration starts Sunday (7/12) 11 am',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'Dear Parents, \r\n\r\nThere will be a virtual vision camp series from late July to mid- September. Most sessions will be held on the weekends. \r\n\r\nUnlike a normal conference, children will attend only the topics that specifically interest them such as dating/marriage; social justice; biblical counseling; and being a Godly man/woman. Anyone between (roughly) the ages of 16 to 24 can participate. \r\n\r\nChildren can have a great chance to meet other 2nd gens from around the world and learn many things in depth for their spiritual growth and have a lot of fun!\r\n\r\nRegistration will go live at visioncampubf.org on Sunday, July 12 at 6:00 am in LA TIME. The spaces will be limited so children are encouraged to register early. You can find more detailed information about the camp from a letter from vision camp director Abraham Lee below. \r\n\r\nThank you. \r\n\r\n================================\r\nDear Vision Camp Friends,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to announce that we will be holding a virtual Vision Camp Series with registration opening on Sunday, July 12 at 0900 EST (2200 Korea Time). The Vision Camp Series will be an opportunity for anyone between (roughly) the ages of 16 to 24 to register for online session(s) tailored around specific topics. Unlike a normal conference, you will have the opportunity to register for and attend only the topics that specifically interest you! Based on feedback from you through conversations and survey responses, we will be offering a menu of topics that we know are of interest to you. You will be able to choose from any number of topics which may include, but are not limited to, dating/marriage; social justice; biblical counseling; and being a Godly man/woman, just to name a few. \r\n\r\nDuring this time of social distancing, it\'s more important than ever to stay engaged and persevere in seeking God\'s vision for your life. Social distancing doesn\'t mean we have to be alone or unproductive or unmotivated. COVID-19 may have canceled our physical camp in Toronto, but the goal of Vision Camp can\'t be stopped. As has been true with Vision Camps in the past, we cordially invite you to more times of \"faith, fellowship, and fun.\" That means offering topics that are timely and relevant to your life and faith. That means most of your online sessions will be limited in size which we hope will allow for more interaction, discussion, and true fellowship. That means honest conversations that are always the most interesting and fun!\r\n\r\nRegistration will go live at visioncampubf.org on Sunday, July 12 at 0900 EST / 1400 London Time / 2200 Korea Time and will close on Monday, July 20 at 0900 EST. As noted above, spaces will be limited so we encourage you to register early. The registration page will include the session topic, speaker info, language (English/Korean), and proposed dates/times. This way you can have all the information you need to make sure it fits into your schedule and register accordingly. The Vision Camp Series will likely run from late July to mid-September. We aim to hold most sessions on the weekends to accommodate participants from different time zones so we welcome everyone from around the world! And we will continue to update the registration page as new offerings become available. That includes a virtual Town Hall with UBF General Director, Pastor Moses Yoon, in late August (more details to follow). I hope all of you will join us for that!  \r\n\r\nIn closing, I am excited for the possibilities that this new format affords us. I am grateful that our global Vision Camp community can stay connected and even grow together during this time of unprecedented challenges. I am hopeful you will come and join us to seek God\'s vision for your life. Thank you to everyone who filled out surveys; helped me with planning; prayed for and supported Vision Camp; and offered to lead a session. I am truly humbled by all of you. \r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, please reach out to me directly. Keep calm, pray, and wash your hands. God bless you!\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\nAbraham Lee\r\n\r\nVision Camp Director',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(13,'notice',-13,1,0,NULL,13,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1598140800,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'UBF Summer Conference program',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'* UBF Summer Conference program\r\n- For brothers : 8/28 (Fri)  7:00 pm- 8/29(Sat) 6:00pm\r\n- For sisters : 9/4(Fri) 7:00pm - 9/5(Sat) 6:00pm\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,'notice',-14,1,0,NULL,14,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'LA UBF',0,NULL,1599955200,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,' Announcement Sept 13, 2020',0,'LA UBF','admin','laubf.downey@gmail.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'1. God asks us to be holy in all we do. The command was given to reward us and bless us. Three reasons are given to motivate us to be holy in all we do. God is holy. God judges each believer’s work. We are redeemed by the precious blood of Christ. Ultimately our faith and hope are in God who raised Christ from the dead and glorified him. He will do the same for us.  \r\n\r\n2. Seek the will of God more than anything else. Think about “What is God doing?”\r\n\r\n3. “If my people, who are called by my name, will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven, and I will forgive their sin and will heal their land.” (2 Chronicles 7:14)\r\n\r\n4. Protection for medical professionals, health care workers, especially our co-workers who are working in the front line of the virus. \r\n\r\n5. Pray for the protection and provision of people who are lacking in their basic needs, especially our co-workers.   \r\n\r\n6. Use our time as foreigners here in reverent fear of God. \r\n\r\n7. Humble ourselves and follow government guidelines including wearing masks and keeping social distance. It is an act of love for our neighbors because we can be carriers of the virus without symptoms.\r\n\r\n8. Prayer government authorities, the president, governors, mayors, health specialists that they may make decisions according to the will of God. \r\n\r\n9. “Rejoice always, pray continually, give thanks in all circumstances; for this is God’s will for you in Christ Jesus.” (1 Thessalonians 5:16-18)\r\n\r\n10. Our chapter name is Los Angeles UBF instead of Downey UBF. It is because we need one name for LA UBF, and people from other places cannot know Downey belongs to LA. \r\n\r\n11. Pray for M. Daniel & Rejoice Shim, and Ezra, and Pearl. I asked M. John Choi to have 1:1 with M. Daniel Shim until he can join a group bible study. M. Daniel will start his first day as RN tomorrow in ICU unit. So please pray for him to be successful in his career. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(15,'notice',-15,1,0,NULL,15,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'LA UBF',0,NULL,1601942400,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We have outdoor worship service from October 4th.',0,'LA UBF','admin','laubf.downey@gmail.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'We have outdoor worship service from October 4th.\r\n\r\nPraise the Lord who blesses us to have in person service. Those who are willing should come and worship together. Let us keep on praying for outdoor worship service. Livestream worship will be still available. We can enjoy both outdoor and home worship together.\r\n\r\n*Pray for personal repentance and God’s mercy\r\n*Pray for world mission and Bible America\r\n*Pray for the help of the Holy Spirit, for God\'s peace and Jesus\' grace to cover us at this time.\r\n*Pray for the well being of the chapter members spiritually, emotionally and physicall\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\nLA UBF Church',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(16,'notice',-16,1,0,NULL,16,0,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'Joseph Cho',0,NULL,1627171200,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'LA UBF SBC 2021',0,'Joseph Cho','admin','whcho@kookmin.ac.kr',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL,'<h2>2021 LA UBF Summer Conference</h2>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Title: Not come to be served, but to serve</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight:bold;\">(Mark 10:45) </p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight:bold;\">8/13-14</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight:bold;\">In person and online (Hybrid)</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<div class=\"justify-content-center row\">\r\n<table class=a border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=717 style=\'padding:20px;\'>\r\n <tr>\r\n  <td width=67 valign=top style=\'width:50.25pt;border:solid black 1.0pt;\r\n  padding:5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt\'>\r\n  <p class=MsoNormal style=\'line-height:normal;border:none\'><span lang=EN> </span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td width=234 valign=top style=\'width:175.5pt;border:solid black 1.0pt;\r\n  border-left:none;padding:5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt\'>\r\n  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style=\'text-align:center;line-height:normal;\r\n  border:none\'><b><i><span lang=EN>8/13(Fri)</span></i></b></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td width=210 valign=top style=\'width:157.5pt;border:solid black 1.0pt;\r\n  border-left:none;padding:5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt\'>\r\n  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style=\'text-align:center;line-height:normal;\r\n  border:none\'><b><i><span lang=EN>8/14(Sat)</span></i></b></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td width=206 valign=top style=\'width:154.5pt;border:solid black 1.0pt;\r\n  border-left:none;padding:5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt 5.0pt\'>\r\n  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style=\'text-align:center;line-height:normal;\